M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 moderately widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 80-82
) 0.62 mm long, symmetrical, fairly strongly sclerotized. Apical process of median lobe almost as long as basal bulb, inflexed, with ventral side straight except near tip, in lateral view gradually narrowed and with acute tip, in dorsal view with blunt tip; articular processes large, prominent. Parameres narrowed from bases to mid-length, posterior mid-length widened, abruptly notched subapically in dorsal view, straight with narrowed, curved apices in lateral view, reaching beyond tip of median lobe. Internal sac without rods or flagellum, with weakly sclerotized, short denticle and scale-like structures.
